    "They observed decreases in slump flow, with a 7.8% reduction at a 10% replacement level using PES and up to a 24% reduction at a 20% replacement level using CESP.",
    "Meanwhile, Jaber et al. [95] and Shiferaw et al.",
    "[96] reported that although TESP and ESP slightly lower workability, they significantly enhance the concrete thermal properties by reducing thermal conductivity by 40% at specific replacement levels.",
    "The results shown in Table 10 illustrate that there are effects of ESP when used as an SCM on various concrete properties.",
    "Several studies have shown that incorporating glass powder in concrete can affect its fresh properties."
